Says Her Passion For Knowledge-Based Entrepreneural Dev Was Legendary IBADAN – The Leader of the apex body of Yoruba Nation Self-Determination Struggle, Ilana Omo Oodua Worldwide, Professor Banji Akintoye, has described the death of first Yoruba Trained Cosmetologist, Chief Mrs Olayinka Abiodun Wright-Osibogun as the end of a glorious era in Yoruba Land. Madam Wright-Osibogun was the Manufacturer of Popular Hair Pomade “Clarissa” in the 50s, 60s, and 70s in Ibadan, the then capital of Western Nigeria. She died today 15th July, 2022 at her Residence in New Bodija, Ibadan, Oyo-State. In a statement he made available to news men through his Communications Manager, Mr. Maxwell Adeleye, Akintoye described Mama Wright-Osibogun as a glorious and virtuous woman whose zeal and passion for knowledge-based Entrepreneural Development was legendary. “Mama was the etymologist of virtuous beauty business in Yoruba Land and a woman whose lifestyle was a model. “She used her creativity and innovation to establish wealth and promoted prosperity in Ibadan, the Headquarters of Western Nigeria through her product, “Clarrisa.” “Mama will also be fondly remembered for giving birth to worthwhile children, including one of us in the struggle for the advancement and development of Yoruba Land, Otunba Ayodeji Osibogun. POLL “Mama shall be missed for her candor, courage and passion for humanitarian development. We shall also miss her for her contributions to the empowerment of the younger generation” Akintoye, said.